'''博德利图书馆'''（{{lang-en|'''Bodleian Library'''}}，{{IPAc-en|ˈ|b|ɒ|d|l|i|ə|n}}，{{IPAc-en|b|ɒ|d|ˈ|l|iː|ə|n}}）是[[英国|英国]][[牛津大学|牛津大学]]主要的[[图书馆|图书馆]]。根据馆藏书籍数量统计，也是英国第二大的图书馆，仅次于[[大英图书馆|大英图书馆]]。同时还是英国与爱尔兰出版印刷物的法定送存处之一。<ref name="ldla2003">Legal Deposit Libraries Act 2003</ref><ref name="llgcuk">{{cite web|url=http://www.llgc.org.uk/aldl/|title=Agency for the Legal Deposit Libraries|work=llgc.org.uk|access-date=2013-10-22|archive-date=2009-02-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090214033511/http://www.llgc.org.uk/aldl/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="s1985">S198(5) Copyright and Related Rights Act 2000</ref> 当其名写作复数时（[[博德利图书馆群|博德利图书馆群]]）不单指博德利图书馆建筑本身，还代表坐落于牛津大学中心及周边的一系列图书馆组成的藏书体系；这个体系的前身是牛津大学文库服务（Oxford University Library Services, OULS）。<ref >{{en}}{{cite web | url = https://www.bodleian.ox.ac.uk/docs/historybodleian.pdf | title = History of the Bodleian illustrated brochure | accessdate = 2019-09-17 | quote = Libraries in the Bodleian Libraries group include major research libraries, libraries attached to faculties, departments and other institutions of the University and, of course, the principal University library – the Bodleian Library | archive-date = 2020-12-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201205175100/https://www.bodleian.ox.ac.uk/docs/historybodleian.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref>

== 读者誓词 ==
[[File:Bodleian_oath_on_a_metal_plate.jpg|thumb]]
根据博德利图书馆的条例，所有新读者在第一次进入图书馆之前都需要做一次类似于读者守则的声明。<ref >{{en}}{{cite web | url = https://www.bodleian.ox.ac.uk/about/policies/regulations | title = Libraries Curators Regulations 1 of 2014 | accessdate = 2019-09-17 | quote = All readers are deemed to have subscribed to, and must adhere to, the Bodleian Library declaration. | archive-date = 2021-01-07 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210107221128/https://www.bodleian.ox.ac.uk/about/policies/regulations | dead-url = no }}</ref>传统形式上。这份声明需要由读者在场口头宣誓，因此被称为'''博德利誓词'''，不过现今大部分牛津学生都在领取学生卡（暨博德利读者卡）时签署了等同效力的合约，只有少数学生仍选择出席图书馆不定期举办的宣誓仪式并口述誓词。<ref >{{en}}{{cite web | url = http://www.admin.ox.ac.uk/estates/ourservices/fm/card/use/ | title = Card and IT Service Entitlements | accessdate = 2019-09-17 | archive-date = 2019-07-17 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190717140613/http://www.admin.ox.ac.uk/estates/ourservices/fm/card/use/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>尽管如此，校外人士在申请成为读者后仍需要在图书馆管理员面前口头宣誓才会获发读者卡。

最早的誓词使用的是传统拉丁文，不过今日最广泛使用的是英文版本的誓词。由于图书馆收藏来自世界各地不同语言的书籍，图书馆也提供包括中古语言在内的超过百种其他语言版本的誓词供其他语言使用者以母语宣誓：<ref name=Twitter>{{Cite tweet |user=bodleianlibs |author=Bodleian Libraries |number=852527378215694336 |date = 13 Apr 2017 |title=We have translated the Bodleian oath into more than one hundred languages. Readers make the pledge in their mother tongue.}}</ref>

=== 拉丁语<ref>{{Cite journal|title=The Bodleian reader’s oath|url=https://bodleianlibs.tumblr.com/post/159530533035/the-bodleian-readers-oath|date=2019-09-18|journal=|access-date=2019-09-17|archive-date=2021-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107221117/https://bodleianlibs.tumblr.com/post/159530533035/the-bodleian-readers-oath|dead-url=no}}</ref> ===
{{cquote|
Do fidem me nullum librum vel instrumentum aliamve quam rem ad bibliothecam pertinentem, vel ibi custodiae causa depositam, aut e bibliotheca sublaturum esse, aut foedaturum deformaturum aliove quo modo laesurum; item neque ignem nec flammam in bibliothecam inlaturum vel in ea accensurum, neque fumo nicotiano aliove quovis ibi usurum; item promitto me omnes leges ad bibliothecam Bodleianam attinentes semper observaturum esse.
}}

=== 英语<ref>Cite journal|title=The Bodleian reader’s oath|url=https://bodleianlibs.tumblr.com/post/159530533035/the-bodleian-readers-oath|date=2019-09-18</ref> ===
{{cquote|
I hereby undertake not to remove from the Library, nor to mark, deface, or injure in any way, any volume, document or other object belonging to it or in its custody; not to bring into the Library, or kindle therein, any fire or flame, and not to smoke in the Library; and I promise to obey all rules of the Library.
}}

=== 现代汉语<ref name="translation">{{Cite journal|title=The Bodleian reader’s oath|url=https://twitter.com/bodleianlibs/status/852527378215694336|date=2019-09-18|quote=We have translated the Bodleian oath into more than one hundred languages. Readers make the pledge in their mother tongue.|journal=|access-date=2019-09-17|archive-date=2021-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107221126/https://twitter.com/bodleianlibs/status/852527378215694336|dead-url=no}}</ref> ===
